81
00:09:07,330 --> 00:09:09,780
Are you really not going to tell me anything?

82
00:09:09,780 --> 00:09:14,200
Thank you for today. You're a good man.

83
00:09:28,960 --> 00:09:31,930
Staff Captain, are you alright?

84
00:09:31,930 --> 00:09:34,290
Who is he?

85
00:09:58,620 --> 00:10:02,910
Is he the man you were trying so hard to find? The 34-year old one?

86
00:10:02,910 --> 00:10:07,460
Instead of bringing him here, you should've turned him over to the police to free you from suspicion of the forewarned murders.

87
00:10:07,460 --> 00:10:10,500
I'll be proven innocent of that charge eventually. But that's not what's important now.

88
00:10:10,500 --> 00:10:12,990
If proving your innocence isn't important, then what is?

89
00:10:12,990 --> 00:10:15,430
Aren't you tired of living on the run?

90
00:10:15,430 --> 00:10:18,530
I'm, too, against handing him over to the police right away.

91
00:10:18,530 --> 00:10:20,470
Doctor, you too? Why not?

92
00:10:20,470 --> 00:10:24,860
