179
00:18:56,730 --> 00:19:01,470
If you hadn't formed your serum,

180
00:19:01,470 --> 00:19:04,830
do you think all would be somehow different now?

181
00:19:04,830 --> 00:19:07,670
It might well be.

182
00:19:07,670 --> 00:19:11,440
I doubt she was completely successful with her experiment.

183
00:19:11,440 --> 00:19:15,150
If she had, she wouldn't be looking for me.

184
00:19:15,150 --> 00:19:17,080
I see what you're saying.

185
00:19:18,240 --> 00:19:22,440
I need some rest. Today has been a handful with many shocking happenings.

186
00:19:22,440 --> 00:19:25,920
It'll be better for you not to stay at your place for the time being.

187
00:19:29,550 --> 00:19:31,480
Are you worried about me?

188
00:19:33,010 --> 00:19:36,570
Why don't you see if you can find a decent hotel around here?

189
00:19:55,940 --> 00:19:58,840
Deputy Chief!

190
00:19:58,840 --> 00:20:02,620
Have you heard from Staff Captain at all?

191
00:20:02,620 --> 00:20:04,860
How did you find out about him?

192
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:08,130
With you guys, nothing's covert about a covert operation.

193
00:20:08,130 --> 00:20:10,700
What about Staff Captain? Is he alright?

194
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:12,560
I don't know either, Dude!

195
00:20:12,560 --> 00:20:14,380
Sir, please.

196
00:20:16,410 --> 00:20:21,290
He's okay. I rescued him yesterday and gave him a ride. I don't know to where, though.

197
00:20:21,290 --> 00:20:24,630
- That's a huge relief. 
 - G-Great job!

198
00:20:24,630 --> 00:20:26,680
I admire you, sir. You are cool.

199
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,940
Saying such silly things.

200
